{% comment %} StompGuard — Modals Section {% endcomment %}

<style>
  .sg-modal-overlay {
    display: none;
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 500;
    background: rgba(8,8,8,0.85);
    backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 2rem;
  }
  .sg-modal-overlay.active { display: flex; }
  .sg-modal {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid rgba(200,200,200,0.08);
    max-width: 560px;
    width: 100%;
    max-height: 85vh;
    overflow-y: auto;
    padding: 2.5rem;
    position: relative;
    clip-path: polygon(0 0, calc(100% - 12px) 0, 100% 12px, 100% 100%, 12px 100%, 0 calc(100% - 12px));
  }
  .sg-modal-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(200,200,200,0.08);
  }
  .sg-modal-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.3em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--chrome-hi);
  }
  .sg-modal-close {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--chrome-lo);
    background: none;
    border: 1px solid rgba(200,200,200,0.15);
    padding: 4px 10px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: color 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .sg-modal-close:hover { color: var(--chrome-hi); border-color: var(--chrome-lo); }
  .sg-modal h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.25em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--chrome-hi);
    margin: 1.8rem 0 0.8rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .sg-modal h3::before { content: '//'; color: var(--red); opacity: 0.8; }
  .sg-modal p {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.9;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .sg-modal ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .sg-modal ul li {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.9;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .sg-modal ul li::before { content: '//'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--red); opacity: 0.6; font-size: 0.6rem; top: 0.15em; }
  .sg-modal a { color: var(--chrome-lo); text-decoration: underline; }
  .sg-modal a:hover { color: var(--chrome-hi); }
</style>

<!-- SHIPPING INFO MODAL -->
<div class="sg-modal-overlay" id="modal-shipping">
  <div class="sg-modal">
    <div class="sg-modal-header">
      <div class="sg-modal-title">Shipping Info</div>
      <button class="sg-modal-close" onclick="sgCloseModal('modal-shipping')">✕ Close</button>
    </div>
    <h3>Processing Time</h3>
    <p>All orders are processed within 1–3 business days. Orders placed on weekends or holidays will be processed the next business day.</p>
    <h3>Shipping Methods</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>USPS First Class (3–7 business days) — most orders</li>
      <li>USPS Priority Mail (2–3 business days) — available at checkout</li>
      <li>UPS Ground — available for larger orders</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Shipping Rates</h3>
    <p>Shipping rates may vary depending on location and priority of shipping chosen.</p>
    <h3>Tracking</h3>
    <p>You'll receive a tracking number via email once your order ships. Allow 24 hours for tracking to update after receiving your confirmation.</p>
    <h3>International Shipping</h3>
    <p>We currently ship within the United States. International shipping available upon request.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- RETURNS MODAL -->
<div class="sg-modal-overlay" id="modal-returns">
  <div class="sg-modal">
    <div class="sg-modal-header">
      <div class="sg-modal-title">Returns</div>
      <button class="sg-modal-close" onclick="sgCloseModal('modal-returns')">✕ Close</button>
    </div>
    <h3>Return Window</h3>
    <p>We accept returns within 30 days of delivery. Items must be unused and in original condition.</p>
    <h3>How to Return</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Contact us via the Contact form with your order number</li>
      <li>Pack the item securely and drop off at any USPS location</li>
      <li>Refund processed within 5–7 business days of receipt</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Refunds</h3>
    <p>Refunds are issued to the original payment method. Shipping costs are non-refundable unless the return is due to our error.</p>
    <h3>Damaged Items</h3>
    <p>If your item arrived damaged, contact us within 7 days of delivery with photos and we'll send a replacement at no charge. Photos and videos will be analyzed for authenticity. AI edited or created photo/video evidence is not acceptable as proof and may result in the denial of your refund.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- FAQ MODAL -->
<div class="sg-modal-overlay" id="modal-faq">
  <div class="sg-modal">
    <div class="sg-modal-header">
      <div class="sg-modal-title">FAQ</div>
      <button class="sg-modal-close" onclick="sgCloseModal('modal-faq')">✕ Close</button>
    </div>
    <h3>Will it fit my exact pedal model?</h3>
    <p>Yes. Each StompGuard is precision-cut and molded specifically for your pedal model using an in house pedal. Make sure you're selecting the correct product for your device.</p>
    <h3>Does it interfere with knobs or switches?</h3>
    <p>No. StompGuard protectors are designed to protect your footswitches and screen without blocking access to any knobs, ports, or controls.</p>
    <h3>How does the magnetic version attach?</h3>
    <p>The magnetic version uses rare earth magnets embedded in the acrylic that align perfectly on the pedal. No adhesives, no tools — snaps on and off in seconds. Disclaimer: Some initial installation of the full cover may require tools.</p>
    <h3>Will it scratch my pedal?</h3>
    <p>No. The contact surfaces are designed to sit cleanly without scratching. We recommend keeping both surfaces clean before attaching.</p>
    <h3>How do I clean it?</h3>
    <p>Wipe with a soft, dry cloth. Avoid harsh chemicals or abrasive cleaners that may scratch the acrylic surface.</p>
    <h3>Do you offer custom sizes?</h3>
    <p>Not currently, but we're expanding our lineup. Contact us if you have a specific pedal model you'd like to see covered.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ABOUT MODAL -->
<div class="sg-modal-overlay" id="modal-about">
  <div class="sg-modal">
    <div class="sg-modal-header">
      <div class="sg-modal-title">About StompGuard</div>
      <button class="sg-modal-close" onclick="sgCloseModal('modal-about')">✕ Close</button>
    </div>
    <h3>Our Story</h3>
    <p>StompGuard was born on stage. After a dropped beer bottle rendered a large LCD screen useless mid-set, we knew there had to be a better way to protect the gear musicians depend on most.</p>
    <h3>What We Do</h3>
    <p>We design and manufacture precision-cut acrylic protectors for high-end guitar effects processors. Every StompGuard is cut to exact specifications for your specific pedal model — no generic solutions, no compromises.</p>
    <h3>Made in the USA</h3>
    <p>All StompGuard protectors are designed and produced in the United States. We take pride in fast order fulfillment and standing behind every product we ship.</p>
    <h3>Built for Players</h3>
    <p>We're musicians first. Every decision we make — from materials to fit to packaging — is made with the gigging musician in mind. Your gear is your livelihood. We take that seriously.</p>
  </div>
</div>

